; Regression test for issue #738: pricemap shows commodities not listed in file
; https://github.com/ledger/ledger/issues/738
;
; Before the fix, the pricemap command emitted nodes for the built-in
; internal commodities ("", s, %, m, h) that are created at session
; startup to support timelog parsing and percentage arithmetic.  These
; commodities are invisible to the user and have nothing to do with the
; journal's price network, so they only added noise to the DOT output.
;
; After the fix, only commodities actually referenced in the journal
; appear in the graph.  This test is adapted from the original report:
; a web of five user commodities (GBP, EUR, $, USD, AAA) connected by
; price directives and an @@ transaction.

P 2012-03-25 EUR 0.83 GBP
P 2012-03-25 EUR 1.32 $
P 2012-03-25 USD 0.75 EUR
P 2012-03-25 AAA $10.00

2012-03-23 * Test 1
    C               20.00 EUR @@ 16.71 GBP
    D

2012-03-24 * Test 2
    E               30.00 GBP
    F

2012-03-25 * Test 3
    G          1 AAA @  $10.00
    H

test pricemap
graph G {
5[label="GBP"];
6[label="EUR"];
7[label="$"];
8[label="USD"];
9[label="AAA"];
6--5 ;
6--7 ;
8--6 ;
9--7 ;
}
end test

; pricemap also supports an explicit moment argument which exercises a
; different code path (filtered_graph with an edge predicate).  The
; vertex filter must apply there too.

test pricemap 2012-03-25
graph G {
5[label="GBP"];
6[label="EUR"];
7[label="$"];
8[label="USD"];
9[label="AAA"];
6--5 ;
6--7 ;
8--6 ;
9--7 ;
}
end test
